Author: Jesse Waid
Subject: Best reddit app/widget
Body: First off, the Reddit mobile site isn't terrible, and so with a Reddit app, what I'm really looking for is a widget. This app has the best widget I've seen - the transparent theme lets me take full advantage of my background, I've set it to prompt Content or Comments upon clicking, and I can switch to other subreddits on the fly within the same widget. Also, this app is donation supported with no ads or paywall! No problems whatsoever, this app deserves more downloads and a higher rating.
